channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Swedish Officials Forbid Removal Of Champagne Bottles From 19th-Century Shipwreck
item.description: Authorities have labeled the sunken ship “an ancient relic” which requires “a clear and strong protection” to remain intact.

item.title: Our Yorkshire Farm's Clive Owen admits 'I made a right mess' as he shares Amanda regret
item.description: Clive Owen, the estranged husband of Our Yorkshire Farm star Amanda Owen, opened up about the reasons for their split in a candid interview

item.title: The mystery of bizarre creature that prowled our oceans 500,000,000 years ago
item.description: It has been nicknamed the 'alien fish taco'.

item.title: Brazil plane crash crew were 'highly competent' and deemed 'fit to fly' ahead of 'death spiral'
item.description: A total of 61 people have been confirmed dead with no survivors after the jet crashed near São Paulo in Brazil in a sickening fireball seen from miles around

item.title: Woman who said her husband chained her to tree for 40 days ‘tied herself up’
item.description: The woman initially claimed her husband had left her in the forest for 40 days.

item.title: Woman shares hair tutorial for 'best up-do ever' that looks 'so good'
item.description: One lady who is helping people spare the expense of heading to a salon for a chic up-do is Instagram influencer Caitlin Eliza, who showed fans how they can master an 'effortless bun'

item.title: The 7ft tall dinosaur statue that is so big you can see it on Google Maps
item.description: How many times have you come across a 7ft tall dinosaur while checking out your old street or hometown?

item.title: Horoscopes today: Daily star sign predictions from Russell Grant on August 10
item.description: Today's horoscope will see one star sign end a long-term arrangement, while another will feel a connection with someone new. These are your Saturday horoscopes.

item.title: Meet the man who builds giant versions of household items, because why not?
item.description: Steve Wainwright said his retirement from the ambulance service first prompted him to take on some ‘creative’ building projects.

item.title: Exact date temperatures to hit 33C as UK weather 'warped' by major storm
item.description: The Met Office says "a band of thunderstorms" is likely to bring an abrupt end to the pleasant warmth the UK has enjoyed this week, during which temperatures reached around 25C
